law.text:
Upon the recommendation of the Secretary, the Board of Public Works may make grants to counties, municipal corporations, and nonprofit organizations for:
The conversion of public buildings or parts of buildings to adult day care centers;
The acquisition of existing buildings or parts of buildings for use as adult day care centers;
The renovation of adult day care centers;
The purchase of capital equipment for adult day care centers; or
The planning, design, and construction of adult day care centers.
